frameDefinitions: An Agent makes use of a Means (either an action or a (system of) entities standing in for the action) in order to achieve a Purpose.
An Entity meets the pre-conditions for participating in an Event.
A stretch of linguistic discourse or a Text that a Communicator produces has a Topic that it is about.
An Agent attempts to achieve a Goal.
frameExamples: The primary <t>means</t> of gas detection is mass spectroscopy .
Conductor software gives us the hands-on <t>capability</t> to provide updates immediately
The dog went that <t>way</t>towards the ice cream factory.
listRoleDefinitions: The Agent uses the Means to acheive a Purpose.
The action performed by the Agent.
The goal or purpose of the Agent.
The <fen>Entity</fen> whose meeting or falling short of pre-conditions is assessed.
The <fen>Event</fen> that the <fen>Entity</fen> may participate in.
The time at which the <fen>Entity</fen> is capable of the <fen>Event</fen>.
The <fen>Topic</fen> is what a <fen>Text</fen> is about.
A set of propositions that is coherent in being about a <fen>Topic</fen>
The <fen>Communicator</fen> is the person who has produced a <fen>Text</fen> on a <fen>Topic</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Communicator</fen> produces <fen>Text</fen> on a <fen>Topic</fen>.
The <fen>Theme</fen> is the entity that traverses the trajectory.
The <fen>Source</fen> profiles the region where the <fen>Theme</fen> has travelled from (i.e. the region where the <fen>Theme</fen>'s movement began).

The <fen>Path</fen> is the region upon which the <fen>Theme</fen> travels. It is any region in between the <fen>Source</fen> (where the <fen>Theme</fen> departed from) and the <fen>Goal</fen> (where the theme will eventually arrive).
The <fen>Goal</fen> profiles the region at the end of the <fen>Theme</fen>'s <fen>Path</fen>. This is the region where the <fen>Theme</fen> movement stops.
The <fen>Agent</fen> makes an attempt to achieve a <fen>Goal</fen>.
The <fen>Goal</fen> is what the <fen>Agent</fen> attempts to achieve.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the attempt occurs.
The place where an attempt is made.
listRoleExamples: White House voices doubts about Aristide's ability <fex>to govern</fex>
In his book, <fex>Smithers</fex> discusses cotton production.
<fex>On the bridge</fex> he attempted to put the wig on.
